  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">IEC Materials Compendium: Promoting Predictability in Shelter and Settlements Messaging</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project uses a consultative and rigorous process to compile and assess existing shelter and settlements (S&amp;S) subject material for quality, importance, and relevance to the activities of the S&amp;S sector. After the core material has been identified, the project provides for the dissemination of information, education and communication (IEC) materials to facilitate rapid development of common messaging in emergency responses. The aims of this project are to establish systems to compile existing IEC materials, including but not limited to &#x201C;one pager&#x201D;, humanitarian construction (i.e., emergency and transitional S&amp;S) guidance, posters and printed documents, and messaging for radio and social media. The project also aims to establish consensus on metrics for summary and review of materials and to compile a multi-format searchable compendium and relevant products.  Lastly, the project aims to actively promote the IEC materials to improve capacity to rapidly provide basic, implementable, technical guidance and consistent messaging in emergency response and transitional S&amp;S operations.</narrative>
  </description>
